  "method_note": "Empirical, read-only. CLUTCH = last 5:00 of Q4/OT within 5 pts (margin measured ENTERING the play via LAG, so go-ahead baskets count). Points reconstructed per scoring play (FT=1; running-total delta==3 -> 3; else 2) \u2014 validated to 0.16 pts/game mean abs error. TS%=PTS/(2*(FGA+0.44*FTA)). Baseline = same players'/teams' NON-clutch minutes in the SAME 2020-2026 clock games. Clutch samples are SMALL: players need >= 40 clutch shots to appear, < 60 flagged thin. Split-half reliability of clutch TS% is r=0.171 (near-zero => mostly noise / heavy regression to the mean). NO leakage (within-window rates).",
